reviewText: If i could go less than 1 star I would. This course contridicts the most basic rules of good business and professional marketing. Some of the notions in this course were absolutely absurd.

The information provided is too basic and not in depth. The expectation that one can go from thinking about domain name to launch to KPIs and PR in this timeframe is ludicrous. I wanted specific comparisons of web design tools and platforms, specific opinions about social media marketing channels, but there were no details, no comparisons. This course is not useful. Neither the presenter nor the other contributors seem to have any expertise to offer beyond that of their own single experience.

T​his course is helpful to have an overview of general business. However, I think it's more inclined to the product-selling  ones, which doesn't apply for me. The zoom chats, although helpful in some cases, were way too short and random.
